Here are both approaches for .NET MAUI Shell navigation:

## 1. Passing a simple string (query parameter)

**Navigate from ProductListPage:**
```csharp
// In ProductListPage.xaml.cs or its ViewModel
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync($"{nameof(ProductDetailsPage)}?productId={product.Id}");
}
```

## 2. Passing the full object (complex data)

```csharp
async void OnProductSelected(Product product)
{
    var navParams = new Dictionary<string, object>
    {
        { "product", product }
    };
    await Shell.Current.GoToAsync(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), navParams);
}
```

## Receiving both on the ViewModel with `IQueryAttributable`

```csharp
public class ProductDetailsViewModel : ObservableObject, IQueryAttributable
{
    private string _productId;
    private Product _product;

    public string ProductId
    {
        get => _productId;
        set => SetProperty(ref _productId, value);
    }

    public Product Product
    {
        get => _product;
        set => SetProperty(ref _product, value);
    }

    public void ApplyQueryAttributes(IDictionary<string, object> query)
    {
        // Approach 1: simple query string
        if (query.TryGetValue("productId", out var id))
        {
            ProductId = id.ToString();
            // Load full product from a service, DB, etc.
        }

        // Approach 2: full object passed via dictionary
        if (query.TryGetValue("product", out var obj) && obj is Product p)
        {
            Product = p;
            ProductId = p.Id;
        }
    }
}
```

## Wire it up

**Route registration** (`AppShell.xaml.cs`):
```csharp
Routing.RegisterRoute(nameof(ProductDetailsPage), typeof(ProductDetailsPage));
```

**Bind the ViewModel** (`ProductDetailsPage.xaml.cs`):
```csharp
public ProductDetailsPage(ProductDetailsViewModel vm)
{
    InitializeComponent();
    BindingContext = vm;
}
```

**Key differences:**

| | Query string | Dictionary |
|---|---|---|
| Data types | strings only | any object |
| URL-visible | yes (`?key=val`) | no |
| Received as | `string` in the dict | original object type |

Both arrive in the same `ApplyQueryAttributes` method — query strings as `string` values, dictionary params as their original types. Use the simple approach for bookmarkable/deep-linkable routes; use the dictionary approach when you already have the object in memory.
